OL,3,CMillion-year-old stone tools found in
OL,4,CUkraine belonged to ancient humans
OL,6,FIt's not clear what species of early
OL,7,Fhuman would have occupied the site at
OL,8,Fthat time, but the study suggested it
OL,9,Fwould have been Homo erectus.
OL,10,FScientists believe the extinct species
OL,11,Fto be the first hominin to have left
OL,12,FAfrica and walk with a fully upright
OL,13,Fgait.JThe earliest human fossils
OL,14,Funearthed in Europe are from the
OL,15,FAtapuerca site in Spain and date back
OL,16,F1.1 million years, according to the
OL,17,Fstudy. In Georgia, human fossils found
OL,18,Fnear Dmanisi are thought to be 1.8
OL,19,Fmillion years old.
