OL,6,FThe shower of radiation as cosmic rays
OL,7,Finteract with the atmosphere can
OL,8,Fpenetrate rock, creating cosmogenic
OL,9,Fnuclides, or isotopes.
OL,11,FScientists measure the rate of decay
OL,12,Fof these nuclides to determine how
OL,13,Flong the previously exposed rock has
OL,14,Fbeen shielded from cosmogenic nuclides
OL,15,Fonce buried below Earth's surface
OL,16,Fwhere the isotopes can't form.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/8
