OL,3,CMillion-year-old stone tools found in
OL,4,CUkraine belonged to ancient humans
OL,6,FMr Garba's colleagues measured two
OL,7,Fnuclides, aluminum-26 and beryllium-
OL,8,F10, found in quartz grains from seven
OL,9,Fpebbles discovered in the same layer
OL,10,Fas the stone tools.
OL,12,FUsing two methods of calculation, the
OL,13,Fresearchers determined they were 1.4
OL,14,Fmillion years old.J"It's very
OL,15,Fcomplicated to process the samples,"
OL,16,FMr Garba said. "You need two to three
OL,17,Fmonths of everyday work to grind,
OL,18,Fclean and separate the sample."
